Russia May Invite Others to Probe Plane Crash, Interfax Reports

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-09-12T18:39:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/russia-may-invite-others-to-probe-plane-crash-interfax-reports.html
Russia  may allow other countries,
whose citizens died in the crash of a hockey team’s plane near
Yaroslavl to participate in the investigation, Interfax
reported, citing Russian air-accident investigators.  A plane carrying Russia’s Lokomotiv Yaroslavl hockey team
crashed during takeoff Sept. 7. The death toll was 44, including
citizens of  Canada , the  Czech Republic ,  Germany , Slovakia,
 Sweden  and  Latvia , the Moscow-based newswire said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  